@NODE "Hints & Tips section"

For all of those who still get some of the patterns with
the wrong colors on the screen here is what you should do:

Take a snapshot from your WB screen with one of those handy grab programs.
If you don't have such a progam you'll have to do it @" the hard way. " LINK "HardWay"} :)

Load it into your favourite paint program, (you'd better have one :> )
now you've got the exact colors on the screen as your WB screen
save the palette for future use.

Load the screen size backgrounds as a picture,
load the palette and save the picture.

For the smaller patterns, load them as a picture,
load the palette, pick up the picture as a brush,
save the brush and you should have a correct looking brush.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HardWay"

Write down all the colors with their RGB numbers, you can find them when
you start your Prefs/Palette program, and alter the colors in the paint
program accordingly.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Templates"
@FONT XCourier.font 13

MUI Program  - Any MUI Program except Prefs, since MUI Programs always
               seem to be commodities I have added the Commodity border here.
Commodity    - The Commodity Programs
Improver     - A program that patches the OS or another program.
Normal       - The default template, for programs or data files.
AmigaGuide   - For specific amigaguide files.

Prefs1       - Default template for preference programs
Prefs2       - If you don't like Prefs1.
MUI Prefs    - For preferences programs that use MUI.
EGS Prefs    - For EGS preference programs.

Disk         - Template for disks, CDs etc.
HD Disk      - I use this one for Disks formatted with the DiskSpare.device.
Image Drawer - Do I have to explain this one???

MultiScan    - I like this one better than the 1084 monitor image.
Mouse        - Better than the image of the A500 mouse.
@ENDNODE
